title: [BUG] mlflow autologging with mlflow skinny broken in recent versions

labels.name: area/tracking
labels.description: Tracking service, tracking client APIs, autologging

body:
### Willingness to contribute

Yes. I would be willing to contribute a fix for this bug with guidance from the MLflow community.

### System information

- **Have I written custom code (as opposed to using a stock example script provided in MLflow)**: no
- **OS Platform and Distribution (e.g., Linux Ubuntu 16.04)**: linux ubuntu 
- **MLflow installed from (source or binary)**: pip
- **MLflow version (run ``mlflow --version``)**: 1.25.1
- **Python version**: 3.7.11
- **npm version, if running the dev UI**: n/a


### Describe the problem

When installing mlflow-skinny and launching `mlflow.autolog()`, an ImportError occurs (see below for trace).
Note that this worked in earlier versions of mlflow skinny, e.g. 1.20.0. 1.22.0 seems to be the last version where it's working.

### Tracking information

_No response_

### Code to reproduce issue

```bash
$ pip install mlflow-skinny
```
```python
import mlflow; mlflow.autolog()
```

### Other info / logs

```python-traceback
>>> import mlflow; mlflow.autolog()
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "<stdin>", line 1, in <module>
  File "/opt/conda/lib/python3.7/site-packages/mlflow/utils/autologging_utils/__init__.py", line 416, in autolog
    return _autolog(*args, **kwargs)
  File "/opt/conda/lib/python3.7/site-packages/mlflow/tracking/fluent.py", line 1574, in autolog
    from mlflow import (
  File "/opt/conda/lib/python3.7/site-packages/mlflow/tensorflow/__init__.py", line 26, in <module>
    import mlflow.keras
  File "/opt/conda/lib/python3.7/site-packages/mlflow/keras.py", line 21, in <module>
    from mlflow import pyfunc
  File "/opt/conda/lib/python3.7/site-packages/mlflow/pyfunc/__init__.py", line 228, in <module>
    from mlflow.models import Model, ModelSignature, ModelInputExample
ImportError: cannot import name 'ModelInputExample' from 'mlflow.models' (/opt/conda/lib/python3.7/site-packages/mlflow/models/__init__.py)
```
